<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4496318>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 1. A–D: Maladera holosericea (Scopoli, 1772) (Germany: Brandenburg: Mecherin); E–H: M. renardi (Ballion, 1870) (lectotype: S. delicta Brenske, 1897); I–L: Maladera spissigrada (Brenske, 1897) (Russia: Ussurisk). A, E, I: aedeagus, left side lateral view; C, G, K: aedeagus, right side lateral view; B, F, J: parameres, dorsal view; D, H, L: habitus. Scale: 0.5 mm. Habitus not to scale." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4496318/files/figure.png" .

